A drug addict teacher in class, scoring a joint, asks:
- What is the name of a flock of fish?
Student:
- A joint!
Teacher:
- Haaa... Pinned, pinned... Sadis five!
The teacher moves on to the second question:
- What is the name of the pack of horses?
A quick-witted student:
- This is also a joint!
Teacher:
- Haaa... Pinned, pinned... Five!
Teacher again:
- What is the name of a flock of sheep?
The next student:
- It's called a herd!
Teacher:
- Bummer, bummer... Sit down two! What's your last name?
Student:
- Shoals!
Teacher:
- Haaa... Pinned, pinned... Sit down five!
